The paper discusses the development of an expert system using belief networks and decision networks, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The system also utilizes HyperCard, a hypertext authoring tool, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also mentions the use of a probabilistic scheme for managing uncertainty, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of hypermedia for information storage and retrieval, which falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and potentially also social media (cs.SI).
